<p>"<b>Heart of Glass</b>" is a song by American <a href="New_Wave_music" title="New Wave music">New Wave</a> band <a href="Blondie_(band)" title="Blondie (band)">Blondie</a>, written by singer <a href="Deborah_Harry" title="Deborah Harry" class="mw-redirect">Deborah Harry</a> and guitarist <a href="Chris_Stein" title="Chris Stein">Chris Stein</a>. Featured on the band's third <a href="Studio_album" title="Studio album">studio album</a>, <i><a href="Parallel_Lines" title="Parallel Lines">Parallel Lines</a></i> (1978), it was released as a single in January 1979 and topped the charts in several countries including the United States.</p>
<p><i><a href="Rolling_Stone" title="Rolling Stone">Rolling Stone</a></i> ranked the song number 255 on its list of <a href="Rolling_Stone's_500_Greatest_Songs_of_All_Time" title="Rolling Stone's 500 Greatest Songs of All Time">the 500 greatest songs of all time</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-1"><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
<p>In the UK it was voted number 19 on <i>The Nation's Favourite No 1 Single</i>.</p>
